# Design System in CMS

## Principle

The current visual identity lives in code (`globals.css` CSS variables). The Payload version must make these values **editable by the end client** in the admin panel, while keeping them **seedable** from the current implementation.

## Current design tokens (source: `app/[locale]/globals.css`)

### Colors
| Token | Current value | Purpose |
|-------|---------------|---------|
| `--background` | `#070708` | Page background |
| `--foreground` | `#F5F0EB` | Primary text |
| `--rfe-red` | `#8B1A1A` | Accent — blood red |
| `--rfe-rose` | `#C4A0A0` | Accent — dusty rose |
| `--rfe-gold` | `#B5975A` | Accent — warm gold |
| `--rfe-gold-dim` | `rgba(181,151,90,0.6)` | Gold at reduced opacity |
| `--rfe-rose-dim` | `rgba(196,160,160,0.5)` | Rose at reduced opacity |

